---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  lang="en"
  description="LaunchDock is a hands-on interactive AI tutorial site: bridging the gap between videos and docs so you can actually get things done."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">About LaunchDock</h1>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Why LaunchDock?</h2>
      <p>
        There's a saying in the AI world: "Get your hands dirty — that's how you learn AI."
      </p>
      <p>
        For CS majors, that's motivational.<br />
        But for marketers, designers, teachers, and freelancers,
        following a tutorial often means more than getting your hands dirty —
        <strong>it means getting completely lost</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Install Python, stuck on environment variables.<br />
        Run a command, get a full page of cryptic errors.<br />
        Google the fix — it's in English and assumes you already know what PATH is.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/nicepkg/openclaw" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OpenClaw</a>
        is a fantastic AI Agent framework, but its documentation is written for developers.
      </p>
      <p>
        LaunchDock exists for people who <strong>want to learn, are willing to try, but need someone to guide them</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>How We Do It</h2>
      <p>Every tutorial:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>📸 Screenshots at every step — no guessing what you should see</li>
        <li>😵 Report "stuck" at any section — we'll know what needs improving</li>
        <li>💬 Ask questions below each article — the community will help</li>
        <li>🧪 Verified with real testing (verifiedAt) — not copy-pasted outdated instructions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Start with OpenClaw?</h2>
      <p>
        OpenClaw's real value is in <strong>integration</strong>: connecting your Gmail, Drive, Notion
        into automated workflows, breaking down information silos — something ChatGPT and Gemini can't do.
      </p>
      <p>
        But we won't stop at OpenClaw. We plan to expand into hands-on tutorials for more AI tools.
      </p>

      <h2>Learning Together</h2>
      <p>
        "Just do it" is great advice. But you don't have to do it alone.
      </p>
      <p>
        Getting stuck is nothing to be ashamed of. This site encourages you to share your experience —
        whether it's a success or a failure. Use the 👍/😵/😢 buttons beside each section to quickly share
        how you're doing; ask questions in the Q&A section at the bottom of each article.
        For broader discussions, join our <a href="/en/#discussion">discussion board</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Who's Behind This?</h2>
      <p>
        LaunchDock is an open-source project built by Joseph.
        If you'd like to contribute articles or improve the site, visit our
        <a href="https://github.com/589411/launchdock" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
        to open a PR or get in touch.
      </p>

      <h2>Teaching & Business Inquiries</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any of the following needs, feel free to reach out:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Corporate training, AI tool adoption workshops</li>
        <li>Course collaboration, content licensing</li>
        <li>Brand sponsorship, advertising partnerships</li>
        <li>Other business proposals</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        📬 Contact: <a href="mailto:contact@launchdock.app">contact@launchdock.app</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
